track_notes: An easy, paved drive to the Bull of the Woods TH in Taos Ski Valley followed by a long, gorgeous hike to the summit. Totals for the loop route shown: 9.9 miles RT with 3200 feet of gain.
track_title: Gold Hill from Bull of the Woods TH

track_notes:
At the E end of Red River take road 578 to the beginning of FR 486. Cross a stream then drive 7 miles up the narrow, rugged, 4WD 486 to the parking area at Goose Lake. 

Hike southerly skirting the E side of the lake to find the start of a steep but well established trail that switchbacks up talus to the top of the ridge W of the lake. Once on the ridge head NW to join trail 64 which leads to the Gold Hill summit. Hike totals: 1.5 miles one way with 1050 feet gain.

FR 486 is popular with four wheelers from Red River and has many narrow sections where meeting other vehicles is problematic. Best to go when traffic is sparse. The 7 mile drive in took us 1:45 with minimal traffic. 

The stream at the very start of FR 486 is spanned by a bridge wide enough for ATVs but 4WD vehicles will need to cross a ford which could be problematic if the stream level is high.

Thanks to NM5S for researching this route.
